{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-challenges-generic-show-tsx","path":"/learn/a2-english-for-developers/learn-how-to-use-basic-programming-vocabulary-in-conversations/task-12","result":{"data":{"challengeNode":{"challenge":{"assignments":[],"bilibiliIds":null,"block":"learn-how-to-use-basic-programming-vocabulary-in-conversations","challengeType":19,"description":"<section id=\"description\">\n<p><span class=\"highlighted-text\">Many</span> i <span class=\"highlighted-text\">much</span> se koriste za govor o količini, ali se koriste sa različitim vrstama imenica. <span class=\"highlighted-text\">Many</span> se koristi sa prebrojivim imenicama, koje su stvari koje možete da izbrojate, kao što su <span class=\"highlighted-text\">apples</span>, <span class=\"highlighted-text\">cars</span> ili <span class=\"highlighted-text\">books</span>. Na primer, možete reći <span class=\"highlighted-text\">There are many books on the shelf.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"highlighted-text\">Much</span> koristi se sa nebrojivim imenicama, koje su stvari koje ne možete brojati jednu po jednu, kao <span class=\"highlighted-text\">water</span>, <span class=\"highlighted-text\">sand</span>, ili <span class=\"highlighted-text\">information</span>. Na primer, možete reći <span class=\"highlighted-text\">There is not much water left in the bottle.</span></p>\n</section>","nodules":null,"explanation":null,"helpCategory":"English","instructions":"","fields":{"slug":"/learn/a2-english-for-developers/learn-how-to-use-basic-programming-vocabulary-in-conversations/task-12"},"questions":[{"text":"<p>Izaberite rečenicu koja koristi <span class=\"highlighted-text\">many</span> i <span class=\"highlighted-text\">much</span> tačno.</p>","answers":[{"answer":"<p><span class=\"highlighted-text\">I don't have much time to finish the project.</span></p>","feedback":null,"audioId":null},{"answer":"<p><span class=\"highlighted-text\">She has many water in her glass.</span></p>","feedback":"<p><